CatDescriptText: Miss Naree Rochanapurananda, of Bangkok, Thailand, Southeast Asia, a student at the University of Pittsburgh, was part of the "Pittsburghers Speak Up" column published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, February 15, 1958, pg. 2 with question: "Should a woman, who has passed the age of 45, marry for the first time?" answer reads: "Yes, I feel that she is more mature and has the reasoning and will make a better companion."
